HEADWORD: Case-bay
<hw>Case"-bay`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Arch.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>The space between two principals or girders</def>.
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>One of the joists framed between a pair of girders in
naked flooring.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

